						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 1505 (1583 A.D.)</hi></p>						

						<p>Records a gift of money which was entrusted to Tirumalai Tiruvēṅgaḍa-Tāttayyaṅgār Tirumalaiyyaṅgār of Śaṭhamarshaṇa-gōtra, Āpastamba-sūtra and Yajuś-śākhā, by Jagatāpirāyar, son of Annama-Nāyaka and grandson of Muttu-Vasavayya-Nāyaka of the Vippra-(?) gōtra, for feeding Śrīvaishṇavas in the Rāmānuja-kūṭam. The details of date viz. <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1505, Subhānu, Tulā, ba. 5, Friday, Punarvasu correspond regularly to 1583 A.D. October 25, Friday; ·42: f.d.n. ·10.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
